I had a meeting with clients and looked this up on google. I called in 3 large pies, a pepperoni, sausage, & mushroom, A "supreme", and at their recommendation, a meatball pizza with onions and peppers. I requested them all extra crispy and indicated I would be there at 11:50. I arrived at 11:45 and two pies were being boxed and the third was coming out. We added 2 large salads, 3 2L coke products, paid and was out the door. One of my clients was a New Yorker and he was IMPRESSED with the pizzas and AMAZED about the salad. All the food was superb, honestly the best pizzas I have had in a long, long while. Fresh ingredients, plenty of sauce and cheese, and I even had the choice or regular sausage or spicy sausage on the one pizza and am glad I picked spicy. So much flavor. They set us up with forks, plates, bowls for the salad, Parmesan cheese, pepper flakes, cups, napkins, and a perfect dose of NY sass that really made my visit a perfect experience. My clients were impressed and LOVED the food and I closed the deal. I will be back again to get some more of this. Awesome.

Passed by this place many times and the scent of pizza wafting as I waked past always got me, so today I decided to go. Walked in and immediately greeted by a friendly gentleman who placed my order, then I moved on to pay. My advice: know what you want because things move quickly here during the week at lunchtime (which is when I went). I got the Number 1, which is 2 slices with one topping and a medium fountain drink. I get my order and I decide to eat outside. This place knows it’s pizza. The inside looked cramped but there is seating inside. I recommend going early during the week at lunch if you can. My slices had the right combination/ratio of sauce to cheese and they were generous with the toppings. Hot, fresh, slightly crispy and you must do the “fold” when eating, never a fork and knife. I will definitely be back, in fact, as I was eating I recommended this place to a guy and his girlfriend who walked past me and asked if the place was good, my response: “This place is awesome.” Bottom line: Rosa’s is pizza at its best.

I am going to say this first it have took me 3 days to write this post. First of all, i take full responsibility of eating here. When this pop up on my google feed and said 4.5 rating and it has gluten free pizza. I trust that they knew what it meant. I walk in and ask for a gluten free pIzza, the guy just put the crust on the pan that had gluten on it. This where i should have walk out (noted that i have walk an hour to get  to this place). 2nd after putting the crust on a sorted clean pan, he used the same utensil to dip the pizza sauce in and use the same gloves. I was just frozen. At this point thr staff was using the same utensil to take the pizza out with the other regular pizza. Again i should have walk out. But to the point i went to the manager and explained that i have Celiac Disease and i noticed that it was too much cross contamination  had happen to make my pizza. He did give my money back with no problem. But after 3 mins later he stated that crust is gluten free and ask what am i exactly allergic to, and  even though the pizza cooked with the other pizza IT WILL BURN OFF THE GLUTEN. THAT BEING SAID I WAS SHOCK. Again i just said very nicely it was cross contamination , but thank you for refund. Do not go there if you have CELIAC DISEASE please. Also the workers behind the scences there was very nice and kind no shade on them. This restraunt seem to have good food for  ppl do not have our issue, but need to educate each other what it mean to have gluten free pizza. We just want understanding of our disease its very hard to find good food to eat.

Simply the best! I have had them catered many times to my office. Everything is on time and soooooo very tasty. I try to get them every chance I get!
My daddy took my sister and I as little girls, I'll never forget it. I'm 30 and headed there today. All smiles
Service is great pizza is delicious, every since my first slice I've been back for more every time.
Best pizza in atlanta
Great Pizza and cool people.
This is New York in Ga
The best!
I can truely say that I'm a fan of Rosa pizza. I'm there every Friday. John, Carl and the staff are great. I must say I do miss Pat.
Great Pizza big slices good prices
Little small reminder of home!
No frills, just good pizza.  They are like an old school pizza place should be.
Even though there is a huge lunchtime rush, the wait is no more than 15 min, the food is nothing but fresh, reasonably priced and the calzones are DELICIOUS...Yum!
Best NY Style pizza in the South!!! I been in and around Downtown for school and work the past 10 years consistently the best service..
Great service and great pizza. Would recommend this place to anyone who wants pizza. They close early though.

Rosas Pizza is amazing!!! I've been a customer for over 8 years. Their quality, value, and service has always been great. I've recommended them to so many people. Try them out once and you won't regret it.

Been To The NY but Never had Pizza There but i have met plenty of People from NY That eats here,so it must be Good To them Also. This is One of My Spots when i go Downtown. I don't know there Name and They don't know Mind but we all know where the Others is from. i am the Cali Kid Always Talking bout my Cali Teams. MOM's also giving a hard time in a good way and POP's is Kool aid and very laid back. Then there's my Buddy Carl/Paul. The Duck/Raider Fan From Portland,Shop talk sports when i come in. So if your downtown Five point,make sure you stop in for the food and family atmosphere.
Awesome pizza...... by the slice
Two slices of pizza and a drink for $6.50. Very busy durning lunch hours so I always go after 2pm. Delicious pizza and pasta and customer service
The pizzas were amazing. Chefs and servers alike are friendly and relaxed, and don't boast of their god-like culinary talents.

I love this place.  It's the perfect little lunch spot while visiting downtown Atlanta.  I always get the two slice special.  Thats two slices of one topping pizzas with a fountain drink.  There is usually a line wrapped around the small ordering space  but it moves quickly.  Many different toppings to choose from.  The seating area is small too but additional seating is available downstairs and outside on the sidewalks.
A little bit of greasy and a whole lot of homemade love goes into these pies. It's worth the lunch time wait.
Soooo yummy and gooey and delicious! I love this place. Convenient to the office and the price is just great! Just got done eating a slice from lunch today!!
Great Pizza!!! I eat here all the time. Fresh out the oven slices are the best.

I absolutely love Rosa's besides the delicious classic pizza, their lasagna and spaghetti are phenomenal. It almost taste like a little Italian eatery. The customer service feel like you are at home and part of the family. The only hiccup is that they are not open late;(

As a Georgia State University graduate, I spent many of my carefully considered dollars at Rosa's. They run a great 2 slice lunch special and I usually ended up taking one home for dinner. Large NYC style slices with authentic taste. The place even feels like NYC.
This place is awesome John is the top guy and treats me like family, his staff is sterling and his food delicious. Good job guys.
Great, fast, tasty pizza by the slice in downtown Atlanta. Moving away has made me miss it all the more.
Great pizza, authentic pace
Pizza was really good, price is affordable for the amount of food you get its a good buy

I grew up in NY.  A good NY slice outside of the tri-state area is hard to come by.  While working on my post graduate studies at Georgia State, I ate at Rosa's quite frequently. Hands down the best slice outside of NYC.

I only go to Rosa's for the gluten free pizza. It's so delicious and satisfying. The pizza is small (10in) but what do you expect for $4.95 and $1 per topping. The staff is friendly and there is always a line wrapped around the corner. Don't worry they move pretty fast.
Just tried the meatball parm. SO GOOD! There was a long line but they moved so quickly I was out in just a few minutes. I'll be going back soon

This is my #1 favorite place in Atlanta for pizza. When you enter during the lunch hour, there's a reason the line is wrapped around the place. Don't let the line scare you, it always moves fast. Great pizza, great family working. Be prepared with your order!

I have been going to Rosa's Pizza going on 10 years! I love everything about this place!! I always receive the best service, even though it can get pretty tight in the line. I've never eaten a bad slice from Rosa's! Best NY style Pizza in GA. Now..their lasagna..Oh MY! Just thinking about it makes my mouth water. Absolutely Fantastic! Great Food..Great Price..Great People!

Been going to Rosas for 10 years now, although not as much as I used to (trying to watch the waste line).  Just went today for lunch, and brought it back to my office.  It's been about 6 months since I had been, and let me tell ya.... IT JUST DOESN'T GET ANY BETTER!  I mean, now days, pizza is way too complicated.  You have "specialty pizzas" and artichoke toppings with arugula garnish.. forget that stuff.. you want REAL NY STYLE pizza, hit Rosas!
